      "mechanism": "deterministic",
      "tool_ref": "dna:tool:01KT0RTRA1GHCHKSWAT0000000",
      "preconditions": [
        "Step 6 produced an open release PR"
      ],
      "postconditions": [
        "all required branch-protection checks are green",
        "GitHub reports mergeable=MERGEABLE (not CONFLICTING, not UNKNOWN)",
        "or: one of the three recovery FailureModes raised"
      ],
      "agent_instructions": "Poll the PR's check-runs API (gh-pr-checks-watch) until all required status checks pass, then poll mergeability (gh-pr-mergeability) until MERGEABLE. The three failure paths are the load-bearing recovery surface: (1) any required check fails → pr-checks-fail (abort + surface failing check + link); (2) mergeable=CONFLICTING → release-pr-conflicts-with-target-at-merge (escalate to founder for back-integrate); (3) mergeable=UNKNOWN after 3 polls (~6 minutes) → pr-open-but-mergeability-stuck (escalate).",
